# Public Google Sheet exported as CSV — fed into the LiveData island.
# Variables prefixed with PUBLIC_ are exposed to client-side code (per Astro convention).
#
# To wire this up:
#   1. In your Google Sheet: File -> Share -> Publish to web -> CSV (entire document or a single sheet).
#   2. Or use the direct export URL:
#      https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/{SHEET_ID}/export?format=csv&gid={GID}
#   3. Copy this file to .env and set the value below.
#
# Sheet shape:
#   - Row 1: column headers (e.g. "Battery V", "PV1 Power", "Cabin Temp", "Timestamp")
#   - Row 2 (optional): "_unit" + each column's unit (e.g. "V", "W", "°C")
#   - Row 3+: data rows. The most recent row is shown.
#
PUBLIC_SHEET_URL=
